Description: Corroded fragment of a narrow copper alloy bar of rectangular cross-section, with a triangular end flattened and flared into a cutting edge, possibly the extremity of a small chisel-head.
Curator's comments: One of the bronze "chisels" of "various shapes" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 26
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 26)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.75, p.184, pl.26)
